“Have you heard about a missing airplane? There's a lot of talk about it.”
I was busy with my task to make my way of work, but my colleague insisted on telling me that there was a missing plane. Initially, I was quite skeptical about the authenticity of the news till she elaborated it. My mind began to think a lot about the situation that could have led to a disaster. I tried to get in touch with one of my friends to see if he was a safe way from the situation. I was relieved to finally confirm later that he was fine. The incident only added to my thoughts of this could be a disaster in the years to come.
To ensure my safety, I got all details about the incident. One of the first things that came to my mind was the recent air crash in Pakistan in a plane of Air Blue during one of my flights which was one week after my friend’s disappearance. He could be missing in such a disaster. I was fortunate to not be part of the incident. I was able to make phone calls to the airline and my friend to get more information about the situation. Eventually a day or two after the incident, I was able to contact my friend. We had a long talk and the relief of meeting him back made me thankful that it turned out to be not in a disaster as I was able to breathe a sigh of relief. As the news spread, I could feel all the air around me charged as if an electrical switch got turned on. It took me some time to adjust and then my heart returned to normal. It seemed in a week's time, everyone had all heard of my friend’s return to India. Although, it felt like a long wait to hear the good news, I was finally safe and alive.
- Author: Shilpi Jain
